Title : Lucrezia Borgia (disambiguation)
Text : '''[[Lucrezia Borgia]]''' (1480–1519) was an Italian aristocrat.

'''Lucrezia Borgia''' may also refer to:

* [[Lucrezia Borgia (play)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (play)]], an 1833 play written by Victor Hugo
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (opera)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (opera)]], an 1833 opera composed by Gaetano Donizetti
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1912 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1912 film)]], an Italian film directed by Gerolamo Lo Savio
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1919 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1919 film)]], an Italian silent film directed by [[Augusto Genina]]
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1922 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1922 film)]], a German film directed by Richard Oswald
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1935 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1935 film)]], a French film directed by Abel Gance
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1940 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1940 film)]], an Italian film directed by Hans Hinrich
* [[Lucrezia Borgia (1947 film)|''Lucrezia Borgia'' (1947 film)]], an Argentine film directed by Luis Bayón Herrera  
* ''[[Lucrèce Borgia]]'', a 1953 French-Italian film directed by Christian-Jaque 
*Lucretia Borgia, the nickname [[Buffalo Bill#Nickname|Buffalo Bill]] gave to his Springfield Model 1866 rifle

